IBRAP Individual Sample Figures

This is to create figure 2. Figure 2 contained some old and new simulations.

library(IBRAP)
## Welcome to IBRAP
individual <- readRDS('individual_samples.rds')

adding together data for supplementary table 3 and for figures 2 and 3

datasets <- names(individual)

clust.methods <- c("PCA_NN:LOUVAIN","PCA_NN:LOUVAINMLR","PCA_NN:SLM","PCA_NN:LEIDEN","PCA_UMAP:PAM","PCA_UMAP:KMEANS","NORMALISED:SC3")

norm.methods <- c('RAW', 'SCT', 'SCRAN', 'SCANPY')

count <- 1

all_results <- data.frame(sample = character(), normalisation = character(), clustering_method = character(),
                          parameter = character(), ARI = numeric(), NMI = numeric(), ASW = numeric())

for(x in seq_along(datasets)) {
  #print(x)
  for(t in 2:4) {
    
    for(u in seq_along(clust.methods)) {
      
      row.nam <- rownames(individual[[x]]@methods[[t]]@benchmark_results$clustering[[u]])
      #print(row.nam)
      for(m in 1:nrow(individual[[x]]@methods[[t]]@benchmark_results$clustering[[u]])) {
        
        all_results[count, 'sample'] <- datasets[x]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'normalisation'] <- norm.methods[t]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'clustering_method'] <- clust.methods[u]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'parameter'] <- row.nam[m]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'ARI'] <- individual[[x]]@methods[[t]]@benchmark_results$clustering[[u]][m,4]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'NMI'] <- individual[[x]]@methods[[t]]@benchmark_results$clustering[[u]][m,5]
        #print('.')
        all_results[count, 'ASW'] <- individual[[x]]@methods[[t]]@benchmark_results$clustering[[u]][m,1]
        
        #print(count)
        
        count <- count + 1
        
      }
      
    }
    
  }
  
}

all_results <- all_results[order(all_results$sample),]

list.of.results <- list()

for(i in datasets) {
  
  list.of.results[[i]] <- all_results[all_results$sample==i,]
  
}

for(i in datasets) {
  
  list.of.results[[i]]$ARI_rank <- rank(list.of.results[[i]]$ARI)
  list.of.results[[i]]$NMI_rank <- rank(list.of.results[[i]]$NMI)
  list.of.results[[i]]$ASW_rank <- rank(list.of.results[[i]]$ASW)
  
}

for(i in datasets) {
  
  list.of.results[[i]]$Score <- apply(X = list.of.results[[i]][,c('ARI_rank','NMI_rank','ASW_rank')], MARGIN = 1, FUN = function(x) {
    
    mean(x)
    
  })
  
}

all_results <- do.call(rbind, list.of.results)

tempo <- strsplit(x = all_results[grepl(pattern = 'neighbourhood', x = all_results$parameter),]$parameter, split = '_')
tempor <- list()
count <- 1

for(u in tempo) {
  
  tempor[[count]] <- tempo[[count]][3]
  count <- count + 1
  
}

all_results[grepl(pattern = 'neighbourhood', x = all_results$parameter),]$parameter <- unlist(tempor)

all_results$Pipeline <- paste0(all_results$normalisation, '_', all_results$clustering_method, '_', all_results$parameter)

all_results$Score_scaled <- 100

for(x in unique(all_results$sample)) {
  
  all_results[all_results$sample==x,]$Score_scaled <- scales::rescale(x = all_results[all_results$sample==x,]$Score, to = c(0,100))
  
}

all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='PCA_NN:LOUVAIN'] = 'LOUVAIN'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='PCA_NN:LOUVAINMLR'] = 'LOUVAINMLR'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='SLM'] = 'SLM'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='PCA_NN:LEIDEN'] = 'LEIDEN'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='PCA_UMAP:PAM'] = 'UMAP + PAM'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='PCA_UMAP:KMEANS'] = 'UMAP + KMEANS'
all_results$clustering_method[all_results$clustering_method=='NORMALISED:SC3'] = 'NORMALISED COUNTS + SC3'

Plotting Figure 2 panel B

count <- 1

results <- data.frame(sample = character(), normalisation = character(), clustering_method = character(), 
                      parameter = character(), ARI = numeric(),NMI = numeric(), ASW = numeric(), ARI_rank = numeric(),
                      NMI_rank = numeric(), ASW_rank = numeric(), Score = numeric(), ranking=numeric())

for(x in datasets) {
  
  for(p in unique(all_results$clustering_method)) {
    
    for(a in c('SCT','SCRAN','SCANPY')) {
      
      int <- all_results[all_results$sample==x,]
      int_2 <- int[int$clustering_method==p,]
      int_2 <- int_2[int_2$normalisation==a,]
      
      results[count,] <- cbind(int_2[which.max(int_2$Score),colnames(all_results)%in%colnames(results)], ranking = 'Max')[,match(x = colnames(cbind(int_2[which.max(int_2$Score),colnames(all_results)%in%colnames(results)], ranking = 'Max')), colnames(results))]
      
      count <- count + 1
      
      results[count,] <- cbind(int_2[which.min(int_2$Score),colnames(all_results)%in%colnames(results)], ranking = 'Min')[,match(x = colnames(cbind(int_2[which.min(int_2$Score),colnames(all_results)%in%colnames(results)], ranking = 'Min')), colnames(results))]

      count <- count + 1
      
    }
    
  }
  
}

get_legend<-function(a.gplot){
  tmp <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(a.gplot))
  leg <- which(sapply(tmp$grobs, function(x) x$name) == "guide-box")
  legend <- tmp$grobs[[leg]]
  return(legend)}

GT_legend <- get_legend(bad_GT)
